Powershell is a command line interface by Microsoft which enables admin and super-users to manage computers from the command line. Its also a scripting language.
Commands are performed using cmdlets. It is a language for doing things not so much creating things as in other languages. 

Powershell relies on the pipeline, passing objects to other cmdlets for input pushing around structured data. 

Benefits of powershell:
Faster
Reduces mistakes
Enhances your knowledge everywhere
One of the most connected communities
Continues to grow and be adapted.

     Some of the ways it is exploited is by hackers who use it to execute actions in memory. A way to avoid this would be wrapping scripts requiring them 
     to be digitally signed. Hackers are learning to use it more and social engineering attacks are still effective as time passes.
